DBA related scripts for managing client infrastructure

Installation instructions:

o Run create_perf_tarball.sh from git/dba.

  It will create /tmp/perf_tarball.tgz which
  can be copied to any host.

o Copy the file to dest_host:/tmp

o On the dest host open the tar file and run
  install_perf_tarball.sh.

  cd /tmp
  tar xzvf perf_tarball.tgz
  cd perf_tarball
  ./install_perf_tarball.sh

o Source the vfa_lib.sh script

  source /usr/local/palominodb/scripts/vfa_lib.sh

o Update /etc/vfatab to have the correct location for all my.cnf files
 
  ie: /etc/my.cnf:3306:Y:Y    
  (Location of my.cnf : the port : Whether to autostart : Whether it should be default instance to connect to)

  or

  # often this will work
  for conf in `ls /etc/mysql/my-*33*.cnf |sort`; do echo $conf:$(echo $conf |awk -F"/" '{print $NF}'|sed "s/my-m//;s/.cnf//"):Y:N;done > /etc/vfatab

o If you want to use the multi instance managing mysqld script do the following

  mv /etc/init.d/mysql /etc/init.d/original.mysql  2> /dev/null;mv /etc/init.d/mysqld /etc/init.d/original.mysqld 2> /dev/null

  ln -s /usr/local/palominodb/scripts/mysqld /etc/init.d/mysql;ln -s /usr/local/palominodb/scripts/mysqld /etc/init.d/mysqld 

